_ What do you know about other feasts, what do you remember?

Speaker: Lamara Oniani-Liparteliani (LS); interviewer: Medea Sagliani (LB). Various feasts and the building of churches in Lentekh. Video 29; (01:01:20:160_01:09:21:720).
merme-merme desascaular i elesile ligem lenexas.
_ igen desascaular ser alyr maqid, tanap i kiob i uliob li.
_ I remember such feasts as: Easter, Qvishoba and Ulishoba.
_ sxva desascaulebi mei eseni maxsovs, adgoma da kvioba da ulioba aris.
uliob gixal lea meles a, ei, uliob, mar sasxen i ixen,
Ulishoba is celebrated in Upper Mele, but people used to ride from Sasashi,
ulioba vicit zemo melei ise ("ase"), is, ulioba, magram sasaidan da qvela mxridan,
tel lx ex esrda i amno, keqana, ei uli li.
from Lashkheti and all other places. That is Ulishi.
mteli laxeti ik midioda cxenit da amiti, kveqana, is uliia.
lagira, dideb otqad, ala lagira... mde..., exnisa naes lok li,
They say, that the icon of St. Kvirike of Kala is taken from there...from Lagurka (the St. Kvirike church)
lagura ("cminda viries saxelobis elesia"), dideba mas ("miuvida"), alis cminda virie... isa..., ikidan caebuliao,
imay ee ardeba, e lagiras, ee ala... mde..., amayb lani ardeba e uli
and now...how it was celebrated there, in that St. Kvirike church, the same happens during Ulishi feasts.
rogorc ik ardeba, im cminda viries saxelobis elesiai, ik alis... isa..., asetnairad ("lanze") ardeba is ulioba
i e bgi desascaul li, d bgi desascaul li.
This is also a great feast, a very great one...
da isic lieri ("magari") desascaulia, alian lieri ("didi magari") desascaulia.
anleb gixal ee, eey ami lidab, anlebs, atxe amalebas xalix.
We also celebrate the Ascension Day and this happens in the same way, too; the Ascension Day is called "Amaghleba".
amaleba vicit ik, ikac ase xdeba, amalebas, axla amalebas eaxian.
mag ale, mag xoa desascaular i ligrgi, giorgoba gixal i ami.
All these...these nice feasts; and Giorgoba...we celebrate Giorgoba (the day of St. George) and so on.
qvelaperi es, qvela argi desascaulebi da giorgoba, giorgoba vicit da ase.
giorgobai a ekad nay desascaul mm gixlda,
We did not celebrate the day of St. George before...
giorgobaze ise ("ase") manamde ven desascauli ar vicodit,
atxe asqi xalx, edo ale gixld', ikm.
but now everybody celebrates it; it was a simple holiday before...
axla qvela desascaulobs ("aetebs xalxi"), torem es vicodit, ai, ukme.
ar eileboda ligrgi lade oaxs, yed nsqas... i s anda dede, trkas, lacxnirs:
It was forbidden during Giorgoba to touch a needle...mother used to hide scissors, combs:
ar eileboda giorgoba des oaxs, an nemss... da qvelapers damalavda xolme deda, maraels, savarcxels:
"nom loku xecadd, sabra, ales lok xoxal umai kam lised
"Don't look at these things, or else your cattle won't come back...
"ar dainaxoto, ("sabralo"), aman iciso sakonlis ("umai{s}") garet darena
i ligrgi erb xoxldax, ere giorg... ea lade xaer mod eykutnnda, mod eykutnnda o
And it was forbidden on Giorgoba to do anything
da giorgobas aralva icodnen, rom im des ar unda gagenria, ar unda gagenria xeli ("oi")
i dsma eysqnda eyalib, ere dageria ei ukm i limae lani i limzr-liqrli, ra tkma unda.
and you were not to do anything... were not to break the holiday; you were not to work and, of course, you had to pray.
da araperi ar unda gageetebina iseti, rom dagervia is ukme da muaobis saxit ("lanze") da locva-vedrebac, ra tkma unda.
momkmed elesil des'rdax eka i titon xalx, sarosld yeru ameu,
There were no acting churches by that time and people themselvesthere were local people - "Sarostas"- who prayed; we had two of them
momkmedi elesiebi ar iqo main da tviton xalxi, "sarosebad" ("adgilobrivi mlocvelebi") ori ak,
k'r oxciln lenxate, eno leksuri lamrias, dideb otqad, een sarosl xeqdax,
When I was married and went to live in Lentekhi...then there, in the church of St. Lamaria in Leqvsuri...glory to itthere were "Sarostas"...
rom gavtxovdi lenexi, mere lekvsuris cminda lamarias elesiai, dideba mas ("miuvida"), ik "sarosebi" hqavdat,
ka lahdin eis abls, tetrs, santels i ka xknin, ere "u lok emmezr amno migi bpar".
You would give them sacred (holy) bread, flour, a candle and say to them: "Bless my children with it".
miscemdi imas salocav urs ("ablas"), puls ("tetrs"), santels da eqodi, rom "damiloceo amit emi bavvebi".
"amno lok atmzr ama bpar, ama qin i dina, mens lok".
"With it may blessed her children, her boy and girl, amen!"
"amit daloceo amisi bavvebi, amisi bii da gogo, amino".
i eis, tetrs, mine... mdatysa.... ddax, qut xunx cale.
And they threw some coins in it... there...they had a special box for this.
da imas, puls ("tetrs"), tavis... imai... qridnen xolme, quti hkonda cale.
And they kept separately the sacred bread.
They had special jugs for wine.
ales s 'ixryldax, tdax eno nebozs, xy xexryelolx ale,

amas qvelapers eagrovebdnen xolme, mere gainacilebdnen xolme saamos, bevri ugrovdebodat es,
lemzezral i ale tetr i ale letre, mag xy xexryeloldax alyrs, yedur xy,
sacred (holy) bread, the money and the spirits...all this was gathered in great amounts...
sepisverebi da es puli ("tetri") da es sasmeli, qvelaperi bevri ugrovdebodat amat, mtlad bevri,
and they usually shared all these with each other...
ei elesia dangreis iras las misul.
is elesia dangrevis iras iqo misuli.
i laxm ertem, dideb otqad, miga ziadis i zurcaxan u, zuros, esalebloba
And God, glory to Him, endowed His mercy on Zviad and Zuro, and they were able to do it
da misca mertma, dideba mas ("miuvida"), ems zviadis da zurostan ertad, zuros, esalebloba

ak, emi saxlis tavze, ldis karapze, salocavi qopila velad.

There was nothing there; just on the Ascension Day the whole region used to gather here...here, where I live in Lentekhi.
araperi ar iqo ik, oond amaleba des egrovdeboda xolme es utxe ak, sadac me vcxovrob, lenexi,

aara utxea, tormei oaxi aris, atkmuli hkonda, adiodnen.
'aesdax ex uns, ayendax, 'xryelol ale yedyeru oax anleb lade,
They used to take a calf, kill it and these 12 families gathered at the Ascension Day.
ahqavdat ("aiandnen") ik xbo ("xbos"), dalavdnen xolme, egrovdeboda es tormei oaxi amaleba des,

da oaxis cevrebi ("cevri") qvelani iqvnen ("imqopeboda"), oond kalebs ar uvebdnen.

mamaacebi ("vaebi") dasxdebodnen xolme, dailocebodnen xolme ("aminit") da locavdnen

something like a small niche...so that to place that icon there and people will pray". That's what I said.
niivit, rom, e, xai rom... isa... imai da xalxi rom ilocebs-metki".

first of all, let's spare money for this".
irvel rigi ak gadavdoto es tanxa".
